WTV format reading code using library created by Stephen Toub. WTV thumbnail reading based upon open-source code by Andy VT (www.babgvant.com) Zip Stream compression using DotNetZip (dotnetzip.codeplex.com) Silverlight ZLib source copyright 2006-2008 Cellbi www.cellbi.com Portions of httpcfg access code taken from UrlAclModifier 2007 Austin Wise Windows Input Simulator by Michael Noonan http://inputsimulator.codeplex.com/ UltraID3Lib, an MP3 ID3 Tag Editor and MPEG Info Reader Library 2002 - 2010 Hundred Miles Software (Mitchell S. Honnert) www.UltraID3Lib.com Logo inspired by the ever-helpful Andy Lisse. Traffic light image by AG Multimedia Studio. A custom build of ffmpeg is distributed with this package under a GPLv3 licence, with modifications by InMethod Software, also released under a GPL licence. See www.ffmpeg.org and www.inmethod.com This build includes an open-source segmenter by Chase Douglas, release under a GPLv2 licence. http://svn.assembla.com/svn/legend/segmenter/ For all relevant GPL licences, please see licence text file in installation folder. The relevant source code for GPL-based components can be found in the FAQ at www.remotepotato.com
